 book introduces the reader to the topic by providing and explaining facts, figures and techniques of analysis. The contributions to the first section of Western Broadcasting examine the general theoretical framework. The articles in the second section map out European media cases. The book's twofold approach is reflected in the accompanying CD-ROM, which also contains examples and hyperlinks.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aMassenmedien. 4aMeinungsvielfalt. 4aUnternehmenskonzentration. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / General.2bisacsh1 aAntoine, Frédéric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBiltereyst, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBink, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCastille, Valérie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCincera, Patrizia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoppens, Tomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Smaele, Hedwig, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDowney, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaak, Kees van der, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaenens, Leen d' , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKlinkhammer, Ruth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOstroff, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPauwels, Caroline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPoulsen, lb, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRegourd, Serge, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 